--For each product category, color, and gender combination show the average list price and name it AvgListPrice. Restrict your result to those category-color-gender combinations whose minimum list price is more than half the maximum list price for all products. Put the result set in order by gender, category, and color. Use a subquery in the HAVING clause. 
SELECT
    p.Category,
    p.Color,
    p.Gender,
    AVG(p.ListPrice) AS AvgListPrice
FROM Product p
GROUP BY
    p.Category,
    p.Color,
    p.Gender
HAVING
    MIN(p.ListPrice) >
    (
        SELECT
            0.5 * MAX(ListPrice)
        FROM Product
    )
ORDER BY
    p.Gender,
    p.Category,
    p.Color;
